sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist Browser
    participant Gateway as Gateway<br/>openshift-ingress<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>(service-ca cert)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant Webhook as Mutating Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant DSPA as DSPA API<br/>8888/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: User Access to Notebook (WITH Authentication)
    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>Auth: OpenShift OAuth
    Gateway->>OAuth: Validate OAuth Token
    OAuth-->>Gateway: Token Valid
    Gateway->>RBACProxy: Forward Request<br/>Bearer Token<br/>TLS 1.2+ (service-ca)
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Check "get" on Notebook CR<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: Authorization Result
    RBACProxy->>Notebook: Proxy Request<br/>HTTP (localhost)
    Notebook-->>RBACProxy: Jupyter Response
    RBACProxy-->>Gateway: HTTPS Response
    Gateway-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: User Access to Notebook (WITHOUT Authentication)
    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>Auth: OpenShift OAuth
    Gateway->>Notebook: Direct HTTP<br/>80/TCP
    Notebook-->>Gateway: Jupyter Response
    Gateway-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over Controller,Webhook: Flow 3: Webhook Mutation (Inject kube-rbac-proxy)
    User->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>annotation: inject-auth=true
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>443/TCP HTTPS mTLS<br/>(client cert validation)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Inject kube-rbac-proxy sidecar<br/>Generate config
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Return Mutated Notebook
    K8sAPI-->>User: Notebook Created

    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Controller Reconciliation
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Notebook CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Notebook Event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute<br/>(in controller namespace)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ReferenceGrant<br/>(allow cross-namespace)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create RoleBinding
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources Created

    Note over Controller,DSPA: Flow 5: Data Science Pipeline Integration
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch DSPA CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: DSPA Event
    Controller->>DSPA: Get Pipeline Info<br/>8888/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Token from Secret
    DSPA-->>Controller: Pipeline Details
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Pipeline Secret<br/>for Notebook
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create RBAC for Pipeline Access
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources Created
